Senbrua 1.0.0 (2026-01-04)
==========================

Initial release of Senbrua - A modern remake of Vocalis, the elegant GNOME sound recorder.

Features:
- Record audio in multiple formats (Opus, Vorbis, FLAC, MP3)
- Playback recordings with interactive waveform visualization
- Rename recordings for easy organization
- Export recordings to your preferred location
- RNNoise-powered noise reduction (toggleable from sidebar)
- Theme mode selection (System, Light, Dark)
- Responsive design - works on desktop and mobile
- Right sidebar with all controls:
  - Record button
  - Appearance (theme mode selection)
  - Preferred format selection (radio buttons)
  - Audio channel selection (Stereo/Mono radio buttons)
  - Noise reduction toggle
  - Keyboard shortcuts
  - About dialog
- Internationalization support

Dependencies:
- GTK 4.10+
- libadwaita 1.4+
- GStreamer 1.24+
- GJS 1.54+

Notes:
- RNNoise noise reduction requires gst-plugins-rs (audiornnoise element)
- Flatpak and Snap builds include RNNoise bundled
